gov.usgs.quakeml.parser

Class GSE2_1

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.quakeml.parser.QuakeMLHelper
      • gov.usgs.quakeml.parser.GSE2_1
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AlaskaHypo, GSE2_0_Bulletin, HypoInverse, SeisSan

    public class GSE2_1
extends QuakeMLHelper
    This class handles elements of a catalog in GSE 2.1 format. It is used to parse and process said event and extends QuakeMLHelper to allow that class to handle the output to QuakeML part.

                               java.lang.String region)
        Parameters:
        time - The origin time
        fixedOriginTime - -1 if unknown, 0 if not fixed, 1 if Fixed origin time flag
        timeErr - Time error in seconds, if < 1000., then no uncertainty is known @param rms RMS of time residual s
        rms - RMS value
        latitude - Latitude of origin (deg)
        longitude - Longitude of origin (deg)
        fixedepi - -1 if not know, 0 if not fixed, 1 if fixed (IN GSE2.1 f=fixed epicenter, else blank
        smajor - Semi-major axis of error ellipsoid
        sminor - Semi-minor axis of error ellipsoid
        strike - Azimuth of the major axis of deg clockwise from north
        depth - Depth of origin in km
        fixedDepth - Fixed flag for depth (f=fixed depth, d=depth phases, or blank)
        depthErr - Depth error in km
        nphase - Number of phases (if > 0)
        nsta - Number of stations (if > 0)
        gap - Azimuthal gap in degrees (if > 0)
        closestSta - distance to closest station (deg)
        furthestSta - distance to furthest station (deg)
        analysisType - analysis flag (a=automatic, m=manual, g=guess)
        locationType - location flag (i=inversion, p=pattern recognition, g=ground truth, o=other)
        eventType - Event type "known or suspected of earthquake, rockburst, induced, mine expl experimental expl, nuclear exp or landslide)
        author - The author of the event
        originID - GSOrigin ID within bulletin generators system
        region - Normally this is a flynn-engdalh from the event line
        Returns:

      • addGSE21Phase

        public GSArrival addGSE21Phase(Event event,
                               GSOrigin org,
                               java.lang.String seedname,
                               double dist,
                               double evaz,
                               java.lang.String phase,
                               java.lang.String time,
                               double tres,
                               double azim,
                               double ares,
                               double slow,
                               double sres,
                               java.lang.String tdef,
                               java.lang.String adef,
                               java.lang.String sdef,
                               double snr,
                               double ampNM,
                               double per,
                               java.lang.String picktype,
                               java.lang.String direction,
                               java.lang.String detchar,
                               java.lang.String mtype,
                               java.lang.String mindicator,
                               double mag,
                               java.lang.String arrID)
                        throws java.text.ParseException
        Parameters:
        event - Event object
        org - GSOrigin object returned when origin added
        seedname - Of the channel
        dist - in degrees, if <0, omit
        evaz - in degrees (azimuth), if < 0 omit
        phase - Phase code
        time - Time of arrival, if null, omit
        tres - Time residual if > -1000., else exclude it
        azim - in degrees observed from station, not used
        ares - Azimuth residual in degrees from station, not used
        slow - Observer slowness, if <=0. omit
        sres - Slowness residual, if <-1000. omit
        tdef - No quakeml equivalent
        adef - No quakeml equivalent
        sdef - No quakeml equivalent
        snr - Signal to noise, omit if <=0.
        ampNM - Amplitude in nanometers, of <=0. omit
        per - Period in seconds omit if <=0.
        picktype - 'a'utomatic or 'm'anual, else omit
        direction - 'c'ompression (positive) or 'd'ilation (negative), else omit
        detchar - 'i'mpuslive, 'e'mergent, 'q'uestionable, else omit
        mtype - magnitude type like 'mb', must match a magnitude add or it will be omitted
        mindicator - No QuakeML equivalent
        mag - Magnitude in whole units contribution of this pick
        arrID - Unique arrival ID
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException
